The National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) has extended the service year of 33 corps members for absconding from their Place of Primary Assignment (PPA) in Nasarawa State. NYSC Coordinator in the state, Abdullahi Jikamshi, disclosed this on Thursday in Lafia, during the Passing-out Parade of the 2021 Batch “A” corps members, stating  1,142 corps members who successfully completed the service year without any disciplinary issue except 33 corps members. “I wish you God’s grace as you enter into the labour market, may you be highly favoured. Passing Out Parade: NYSC Charges Corps Members To Remain Worthy… Group Endorses NYSC Trust Fund Bill, Hails Reps “For those of you who have decided to be entrepreneurs and not job seekers, may you be equally fruitful in your endeavours,” Jikamshi said.